Relax ONNX Runtime's abseil version gate so the openSUSE system abseil-cpp can be
used instead of the bundled 20250814 source.  Abseil's CMake config is ExactVersion
(no cross-LTS ABI), so the upstream "FIND_PACKAGE_ARGS 20250814" rejects any other
system abseil.  Dropping the version lets find_package(absl) accept whatever abseil
Factory currently ships -- ONNX Runtime is source-compatible with it (NixOS and
Fedora both build onnxruntime against abseil 20260107).

diff --git a/cmake/external/abseil-cpp.cmake b/cmake/external/abseil-cpp.cmake
--- a/cmake/external/abseil-cpp.cmake
+++ b/cmake/external/abseil-cpp.cmake
@@ -41,7 +41,7 @@ onnxruntime_fetchcontent_declare(
     URL_HASH SHA1=${DEP_SHA1_abseil_cpp}
     EXCLUDE_FROM_ALL
     PATCH_COMMAND ${ABSL_PATCH_COMMAND}
-    FIND_PACKAGE_ARGS 20250814 NAMES absl
+    FIND_PACKAGE_ARGS NAMES absl
 )

 onnxruntime_fetchcontent_makeavailable(abseil_cpp)
